DISTRIBUTION: 
<collectingCountry box="[372,436,227,250]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[490,585,227,250]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(new record, 
<figureCitation box="[737,818,227,250]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="13.[578,591,1438,1459]" captionTargetBox="[153,1067,227,1373]" captionTargetId="figure-47@13.[153,1067,226,1373]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIG. 32 Currently known Hersilia localities in Thailand." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5822828" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5822828/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). As 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[875,1005,228,251]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundaica">
<emphasis box="[875,1005,228,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">H. sundaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is apparently widely distributed. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[820,884,259,282]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and, as the first new record since its original description, is here documented from a forest in northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[218,316,323,346]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Thailand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
